An Act requiring photo ID’s to vote.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 76B, Chapter 54 of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the following
2 subsection:-
3 (c) -- Any person who seeks to vote in a public election is required to establish his or her
4 qualifications to vote by providing a current valid photo form of identification to election
5 officials prior to voting. Acceptable forms of photo identification provided is either a current
6 driver’s license, a government employee card, a pilot’s license, military identification, a
7 Medicaid or Medicare card, and for students, a photo identification university card.
